<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="ida8073008-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5" identifier="/us/usc/t10/s750"><num value="750">§ 750.</num><heading> Command: retired officers</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">A retired officer has no right to command except when on active duty.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="ida8073009-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/96/513/tI/s108">Pub. L. 96–513, title I, § 108</ref>, <date date="1980-12-12">Dec. 12, 1980</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/94/2870">94 Stat. 2870</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="ida807300a-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="ida807300b-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="ida807300c-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section effective <date date="1981-09-15">Sept. 15, 1981</date>, but the authority to prescribe regulations under this section effective on <date date="1980-12-12">Dec. 12, 1980</date>, see <ref href="/us/pl/96/513/s701">section 701 of Pub. L. 96–513</ref>, set out as an Effective Date of 1980 Amendment note under <ref href="/us/usc/t10/s101">section 101 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
